window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>My husband has a son I never knew about. Now he’s in our home. And I don’t know if I’m safe.</p> <p>I thought I had the perfect life. A beautiful home. A handsome, successful husband. He’s a decade older than me, but doesn’t look it.</p> <p>Then TJ showed up.</p> <p>He's eighteen, claims to be my husband's son, and needs a place to stay. I didn’t even know Bennett had a child, let alone one so close to my own age. But he’s family, and I have no choice but to let him in.</p> <p>The next day, a local girl is found dead in our community pool. And guess who’s the prime suspect? TJ.</p> <p>He insists he’s innocent. Bennett defends him. But something feels off, and I’m starting to question everything — my husband, my stepson . . . even myself.</p> <p>Can I trust the people I love? Or is the nightmare just beginning?</p> <p>Please note this book was previously published as My Husband’s Son.</p> <p>This absolutely addictive psychological thriller packed full of twists is perfect for fans of Daniel Hurst, Freida McFadden, Valerie Keogh and Cole Baxter.</p>"; 
